# TypeScript Safety Standards

- Never introduce `any`; prefer `unknown` + narrowing when needed.
- Keep strict typing at module boundaries (props, function params, return types).
- Avoid implicit behavior; model domain concepts with explicit types.
- If type information is missing, ask for clarification before inventing types.
- Preserve existing architecture and naming unless a change is explicitly requested.
